Chapter 1 - Getting Started.
In this chapter you will learn how to produce library file, and how to use it.


hello.c           - First of many "Hello World" programs in this book.

fred.c and bill.c - Source code files containing static library functions.

lib.h             - Library header file declaring the functions in fred.c and bill.c.

program.c         - Program that uses lib.h.

lib.a             - Result of archiving the functions in fred.c and bill.c.


